 made with the brush edge at an angle of less than 30 degrees to the writing line (rustica). All letters, except the last \"a\" in column 2, line 8, are rubricated, but most of the colour appears too bright to be ancient (and appears identical to that with which the inventory number on the lower left corner has been applied); it also appears that not all the interpuncts have been rubricated.",[168,171,174,179,182,185],{"type":35,"l":169,"from":37,"to":37,"h":170,"unit":38},"Line a 1","33",{"type":35,"l":172,"from":42,"to":42,"h":173,"unit":38},"Line a2","28",{"type":35,"l":175,"from":176,"to":177,"h":178,"unit":38},"columns b, c, codicil","line3","line9","11",{"type":40,"l":180,"from":37,"to":42,"h":181,"unit":38},"Interlineation line a1 to a2","13",{"type":40,"l":183,"from":42,"to":176,"h":184,"unit":38},"Interlineation line a2 to bc1","10",{"type":40,"l":186,"from":176,"to":177,"h":187,"unit":38},"Interlineation columns b, c, codicil","6",{"_":189,"notBefore":190,"notAfter":191,"evidence":192},"21—25 CE",21,25,"prosopography",[194,197],{"_":195,"type":50,"ref":196},"Eryx","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462201",{"_":198,"type":54,"ref":199},"Erice","http://sws.geonames.org/2524815",[201],[202,203],38.03785,12.58778,"Trapani",{"_":206,"role":64,"ref":207},"Museo Regionale Agostino Pepoli","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/105",{"_":209,"type":210},"5227","inventory",{"_":67,"mainLang":68,"languages":212},[67],{"n":71,"url":214,"height":215,"width":216,"desc":217,"surfaceType":76},"ISic000537_tiled.tif","3840px","5760px","Photo C. Vacanti with the collaboration and permission of the Museo Regionale di Trapani Agostino Pepoli",[],[220,221,222,81,223,80,224,225,226,227,228,79,229,230,231,232,232,233],"Muscolino, 2013, Mommsen, Bardt, Hernandez di Carrera e l’iscrizione degli Apronii di Erice (CIL X, 7257)","Oliveri, 2009, Le iscrizioni latine","Manganaro, 1987, Tacfarinas e la Sicilia (ovvero L. Apronius e il santuario ericino","CLE, 1844-1897","Mommsen, 1872-1